Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.

reviewText: D. Gray-Man is a fantastic anime about a young man named Allen Walker; who has a demon curse. Allen joins a group of exorcists that fight the Millennium Earl. The Millennium Earl is a demon who seeks to destroy the world by filling it with evil spirits. Allen Walker and his friends embark on a bloody battle to save innocent lives. D. Gray-Man is a very different series. The Gothic mixed with the supernatural creates a unique atmosphere. There are also lots of great characters, good and evil. Character development is the "bread and butter" of this anime. There are also many other awesome points: top notch animation, good soundtrack, and suspenseful action, as well as plenty of comic relief. If you are an anime fan and haven't watched this, I really want you give it a shot. It's very good.
Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.

reviewText: While the price of the series is reasonable it's also a little sad and annoying as we won't get to see the rest of the series as Funimation apparently has decided that the series is not financially worth continuing with.  Still the series is entertaining and exciting to watch as well getting more screen time with the endearing cast.  This actually has to be one of the few series that I felt the dubbed cast surpassed the subbed cast especially for the voice of Alan Walker.  The animation and soundtrack fit nicely and overall the season itself is worth getting regardless of the cancellation from Funimation for anymore of the series.  So if you have the first season I say complete your collection for the most part with this set to add to your anime collection....
summary: Nice Addition For The First Season But Sadly We Don't See The Conclusion To This Seasons Finale
Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.

reviewText: If you are going for buying season 2, I'm going to assume you've been watching season 1 so I don't need to explain the anime for you. The story progresses into killing many akuma and characters that you loved in the first season come back with their own side stories in the second season.Packaging was great and this anime has become one of my favorites. Dark story, comedy, and a top notch cast of vocal actors.
summary: Just as good as the first season.
Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.

reviewText: This is just the first season (51 episodes) ... where's the real season 2 (another 52 episodes)?Great series but as usual Funimation has screwed the fan of this series over.  This reminds me of Deadman Wonderland ... why bother releasing a series that's incomplete or that you have no intention of finishing?  What a complete waste of time on my part.  If I had known prior to buying the series that it was unfinished and was going to stay that way, I wouldn't even have bothered getting into the series to begin with ... what a let down!Guess well never see the episode "Raid" huh?  Why do I feel like I've been scammed again?Steer clear of this anime series ... it's just another one of Funimation's half baked scams .... spend your money elsewhere on a complete series instead!
Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.

reviewText: The Story continues with your favorite Exorcist Allen Walker. The Millennium Earl is on the move with his plans to destroy the world. And it's up to the Black Order to try and stop him. Allen Walker is currently in search for his master. (who is currently missing or, just running away from his duties like always.) There are a lot more fights in this season and the enemies plan is still a mystery. I wish there was more coming out but, sadly no. I guess I have to watch online just like everyone else.
Title: D. Gray-man: Season 2 S.A.V.E.
